How: I found a parking space near my destination, but I had to drive around to find it.
Comments: I think the fishermen that park in this lot take up a lot of space, as well as the people that park here for months (no fault of their own).  Weekdays- parking is not bad if you are going to the waterfront, but weekends are Bad, especially during summer, The parking spaces for the Berkeley police should be used as overflow. Improved signs and wayfinding would be good. Fishing/fishermen parking should be pushed to overflow. No paid parking Please. There are people that have worked (volunteer) for over 20 years at the marina. Parking is important but paid parking would destroy the meaning of Berkeley's water recreation (sailing, swimming, windsurfing at the affordable prices for those that cannot afford or have access to these activities)

ResidenceBerk: West of Shattuck Street
How: I found parking quickly near my destination.
IdeaDriveOnly: I will only drive to Waterfront
Comments: I am shocked that the parking lot next to HsLordships has been locked to waterfront visitors and recreation activity and taken over by the public works department.  Ditto for L&M lots taken over by the parking police.  I will be submitting a complaint to BCDC.  There is enough parking to accommodate recreation and I am adamantly opposed to the WETA ferry.  I am also opposed for Berkeley letting any ferry riders have free parking.  I am opposed to making recreational users pay for parking when they often bring things to carry for the activity (dogs, gear, picnic items, e.g.).  The Genentech ferry pays the city well for parking, as they should.  But this ferry is often empty.  Go figure.  Preserve low-cost access to the waterfront and don't overcommercialize it.
